raymond albert wheeler july 31 1885 peoria illinois february 9 1974 lieutenant general united states army 
graduate united states military academy 1911 
autumn 1943 appoint south east asia command seac asian theatre world war ii staff admiral lord louis mountbatten serve principal administrative officer february 1944 deputy supreme allied commander replace general vinegar joe stilwell 
serve chief engineers united states army corps engineers october 4 1945 february 28 1949 
direct clearing suez canal follow 1956 suez crisis 
wheeler military award include silver star distinguished service medal two oak leaf cluster legion merit 
also honorary knight british empire 
die february 9 1974 washington bury arlington national cemetery 
